title: Average retail price for eggs in Canada 2019
summary: This graph shows the Average retail price of eggs measured in dollars per dozen for each Month of the year 2019 in Canada .
The lowest price point was in March and the highest price was in September .
gold: The graph shows the average retail price ( Dollars/dozen ) for eggs in Canada during 2019 . In general , there is a steady upward trend of the price from January to October , and levels off from October to December , at about 3.37 . There is some oscillation From January to April , and the lowest price is recorded in January .
